#. Tag: title
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation on hardware not supported at release"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: meta
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Learn how to successfully deploy and install SUSE on newer hardware using "
"the provided kernel update ISO images, which offer updated kernels "
"specifically"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With some newer hardware, the installation medium of &productname; cannot "
"boot. This can be the case when the hardware did not exist at the time of "
"the release of &productname;. For such a situation &suse; provides "
"<emphasis>Kernel Update ISO</emphasis> ( <emphasis>kISO</emphasis> ) images. "
"This chapter describes how to use the kernel update to install &productname; "
"on current hardware."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: date
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "2022-02-11"
msgstr "2022-02-11"

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download kernel update"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Kernel Update ISO</emphasis> images are available on the "
"&soliddriver; home page. Use <link xlink:href=\"https://drivers.suse.com\"/> "
"to search for bootable ISO images for your vendor and operating system "
"version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can download the full ISO image or only the <literal>initrd</literal> "
"and <literal>linux</literal> files. The ISO usually needs to be copied to a "
"&usbflashdrive; or burned to a DVD. The <literal>initrd</literal> and "
"<literal>linux</literal> files can be used for a PXE boot. For details about "
"booting via PXE, see <xref linkend=\"cha-deployment-prep-pxe\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boot kernel update"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use the kernel update, boot from the &usbflashdrive; or via PXE. When the "
"<literal>linux</literal> and the <literal>initrd</literal> are loaded, you "
"will be asked to insert the installation medium."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_kernelupdate.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use the boot parameters described in <xref linkend=\"cha-boot-"
"parameters\"/> . This allows using other installation sources than the "
"installation &usbflashdrive;."
msgstr ""
